Former Prime Minister Yasuhiro Nakasone of Japan passed away in Tokyo on Friday. President Donald Trump and First Lady Melania Trump offer their deepest condolences to the people of Japan and to Nakasone's loved ones. Nakasone was praised by President Ronald Reagan as a friend, wise colleague, and leader of America's most important partner and ally in the Pacific. His efforts to strengthen the US-Japan alliance and promote democratic governance in Asia laid the foundation for the global partnership between the two countries, which is crucial for peace, prosperity, and freedom in the Indo-Pacific region and beyond.